Run Flows in User Context via REST API (Release Update)

A flow that runs via REST API uses the running user’s profile and permission sets to determine the object permissions and field-level access of the flow.

This change applies to Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic in Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions.

Salesforce is scheduled to re-enforce this update in Winter ’25. To get the major release upgrade date for your instance, go to Trust Status.

A flow that runs via REST API previously ran in system context, allowing it to access and modify all data. With this update, the flow runs in the context of the user who is authenticated via REST API.

This update improves security by preventing unintentional creation or editing of records by users without permission.

To review this update, from Setup, enter Release Updates, and select Release Updates. Follow the testing and activation steps.
